```json
{
"application": "Aegean",
"software": [
"aprun",
"sed",
"head",
"tail",
"ls",
"if",
"echo"
],
"resource_requirements": {
"account": "mwasci",
"partition": "gpuq",
"time": "01:30:00",
"nodes": 1,
"mem": "32gb",
"output": "/home/phancock/queue/prior_fit_WEEK.sh.o%A_%a",
"error": "/home/phancock/queue/prior_fit_WEEK.sh.e%A_%a",
"array": "1-20"
},
"environment_variables": [
"PATH",
"PYTHONPATH"
],
"data_directory": "/scratch2/mwaops/phancock",
"project": "G0008",
"week": "WEEK"
}
```

This script runs the Aegean application, a tool for radio interferometric data analysis. The script uses several other tools such as aprun, sed, head, tail, ls, if, and echo for various tasks. 

The script utilizes SLURM for resource allocation and management, requesting resources such as an account, partition, time, nodes, memory, output, error, and array. It also sets up environment variables PATH and PYTHONPATH for the Aegean software. The script defines a function called `doit` which uses aprun to run Aegean with specified number of processes and threads. It utilizes data from a specific directory and project, and iterates through different frequency bands for image analysis using Aegean. The script checks for existing output files and processes them accordingly.
